1
00:00:08,083 --> 00:00:09,416
[grunts]

2
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,708
♪

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,458
-[gasps]
-No way.

4
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,416
[BOTH groan]

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,541
This is starting
to get troublesome.

6
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:26,208
Please stop this.

7
00:00:26,291 --> 00:00:28,333
Maybe I should just
kill all of you now.

8
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:30,000
Souma, stop it!

9
00:00:30,083 --> 00:00:31,333
Tch.

10
00:00:31,416 --> 00:00:32,708
More to the point.

11
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:35,708
Why the hell
are you still alive?!

12
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:38,833
[gunshots]

13
00:00:40,166 --> 00:00:42,041
[TAKUYA gasps]

14
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:44,791
♪

15
00:00:44,875 --> 00:00:46,416
[grunts softly]

16
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:47,833
Well, what have we here?

17
00:00:52,166 --> 00:00:53,833
Long time, no see...

18
00:00:55,125 --> 00:00:56,291
Akira.

19
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,833
♪

20
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:35,958
[YOSHIAKI gasps]

21
00:02:37,041 --> 00:02:38,416
Tama-shi?

22
00:02:40,875 --> 00:02:42,333
[TAKUYA]
There's no time to explain.

23
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,375
[grunts]

24
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:50,625
Are you guys planning
to fight me or what?

25
00:02:50,708 --> 00:02:53,375
[YUKI]
Please open your eyes, Souma!

26
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:56,291
If anyone's daydreaming here,
it's you.

27
00:03:00,458 --> 00:03:02,166
[groaning]

28
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:06,750
[gasps]

29
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,125
[BOTH gasp]

30
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:09,708
[panting]

31
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:14,333
[groaning]

32
00:03:14,416 --> 00:03:17,458
[SOUMA] Yeah, like I thought,
you don't get it at all.

33
00:03:17,541 --> 00:03:18,958
Do you, sis?

34
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:25,208
Your presence just annoys me
for some reason.

35
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:30,375
[grunts]

36
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:31,750
[gasps]

37
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,875
Listen, if you can't do
anything to help,

38
00:03:33,958 --> 00:03:35,541
just stay down.

39
00:03:41,458 --> 00:03:42,708
[panting]

40
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:44,750
[SOUMA laughs]

41
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:47,375
[SOUMA] Well, come on,
let's finish this.

42
00:03:55,166 --> 00:03:56,333
[grunts in effort]

43
00:03:57,958 --> 00:03:59,958
Why are you even trying?

44
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:02,375
[YUKI gasping]

45
00:04:02,458 --> 00:04:04,791
[YUKI] If only he didn't have
that artifact.

46
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:09,625
Yuki and I were both caught up
in the Lost, but we survived.

47
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,500
That means we're special.

48
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:13,958
We were meant
for something better.

49
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:17,041
Unlike you, a wimp who couldn't
even protect himself.

50
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:20,666
[panting]

51
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:22,583
-[YOSHIAKI] Hey, you okay?
-Huh?

52
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:24,208
Here, let me see.

53
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:34,000
Sorry, I wasn't able to
completely erase the wound.

54
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:39,041
[JACK gasps]

55
00:04:39,125 --> 00:04:42,041
So you have the same power
as our leader.

56
00:04:42,125 --> 00:04:44,458
Hold on. Is it possible
you're the boss'...

57
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:46,458
Where's my brother?

58
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:48,166
Hmm.

59
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:50,625
[RUI]
He'll be back with us soon.

60
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:53,625
No doubt. The boss
will most definitely return.

61
00:04:55,666 --> 00:04:58,000
[panting]

62
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:01,125
[grunts in effort]

63
00:05:01,208 --> 00:05:03,541
♪

64
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:07,625
[YOSHIAKI yelling]

65
00:05:07,708 --> 00:05:09,333
[groans in pain]

66
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:11,250
[groans, gasps]

67
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:12,791
I'm a little busy right now,

68
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:15,208
but I'll take my time
with the rest of you later.

69
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:18,291
[SOUMA gasps]

70
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,791
[gasps deeply]

71
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:27,750
[groans weakly]

72
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:31,000
[gasps]

73
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:32,416
It worked.

74
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,916
Nah. I'm kidding.

75
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,791
Since it would appear
that none of you have a clue...

76
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:44,458
allow me to be the one
to enlighten you.

77
00:05:45,833 --> 00:05:46,916
[gasps]

78
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:53,166
You have Tsuki's Tears.

79
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,166
[scoffs]

80
00:05:55,958 --> 00:05:58,208
♪

81
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:08,166
[YOSHIAKI]
Brother?

82
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,625
[gasps]

83
00:06:09,708 --> 00:06:11,708
-It's the boss!
-He's back?

84
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:15,541
[panting]

85
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,583
[TAKUYA]
Damn it!

86
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:22,041
Tsubasa?

87
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:25,458
♪

88
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,333
[groaning sharply]

89
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:34,541
[gasps]

90
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:36,500
Akira!

91
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:37,791
Oh, no.

92
00:06:39,916 --> 00:06:41,041
[ALL gasp]

93
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:45,833
[rumbling]

94
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:51,541
He's here.

95
00:06:51,625 --> 00:06:53,583
[panting]

96
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:58,041
[YUKI gasps]
Oh, no!

97
00:06:58,125 --> 00:07:00,041
[panting]

98
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:03,750
This is some kinda
shitty reunion,

99
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:05,541
wouldn't you say?

100
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:07,375
[RUI]
No, something's wrong.

101
00:07:07,458 --> 00:07:10,166
That guy can't be him.

102
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,916
[growls]

103
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:15,916
♪

104
00:07:17,583 --> 00:07:19,125
Damn it to hell.

105
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:21,333
Well, there goes the last
of my severance pay.

106
00:07:21,416 --> 00:07:24,916
Ten years at the factory
and they give you 30,000 yen.

107
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,250
That's a straight-up insult,
Kankichi.

108
00:07:28,375 --> 00:07:32,041
I don't need the opinion
of a guy who lives in net cafes.

109
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:33,958
You just hurry up
and find a job.

110
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:36,166
Yeah, I've been looking.

111
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:39,291
Problem is, though,
for outcasts like you and me,

112
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:42,250
the only jobs available
are super-shitty ones.

113
00:07:43,791 --> 00:07:45,916
Hey, what do you think,

114
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,833
should we do it
for real, or what?

115
00:07:49,291 --> 00:07:51,000
-Huh?
-[machine thuds]

116
00:07:51,083 --> 00:07:53,583
[MAN 1]
Shit. What the hell, man?!

117
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:56,041
You think you can
pull one over on me?

118
00:07:56,125 --> 00:07:57,166
-[MAN 1 grunts]
-[machine thuds]

119
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,958
Give me back my money, damn it.

120
00:07:59,041 --> 00:08:01,750
-[MAN 1 grunting]
-[machine thuds]

121
00:08:02,875 --> 00:08:05,208
You've gotta be
freakin' kidding me!

122
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:06,666
Stupid machine.

123
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:09,041
[JACK] You're pretty noisy
over here, old man.

124
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,375
Huh?

125
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:12,750
[JACK] What'd that machine
ever do to you?

126
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:15,083
[RUI]
Leave your wallet and get out.

127
00:08:15,166 --> 00:08:16,000
Huh?!

128
00:08:17,291 --> 00:08:18,916
-[onlookers gasp]
-[murmuring]

129
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,541
Hey, what are you trying to do?

130
00:08:21,625 --> 00:08:24,000
Think you can scare me
with that little toy?

131
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:25,958
-[RUI] Huh?
-[MAN 1, mockingly] "Huh?"

132
00:08:26,041 --> 00:08:28,458
You got
some kinda problem, trash?

133
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:31,916
Why don't you try going out
and working for money?

134
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Well? Answer me, kid.

135
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,750
It's because of garbage
people like you that the world--

136
00:08:38,916 --> 00:08:40,375
[MAN 1 gasping in disbelief]

137
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:45,083
[screaming]

138
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:47,000
[MAN 2]
He sliced his tie.

139
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,166
[murmuring]

140
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:52,166
-[MAN IN COAT laughing]
-Huh?

141
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:56,208
[MAN 3]
What the hell?

142
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:57,916
That thing's just a toy.

143
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,625
So what was the other guy
screaming about, then?

144
00:09:00,708 --> 00:09:03,166
-[MAN 4] How stupid.
-[WOMAN] Let's get out of here.

145
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:06,958
Huh?

146
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:13,375
[RUI]
Hey. Wait up a second.

147
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,083
Oh, it's you guys.

148
00:09:18,166 --> 00:09:20,666
Well? What was that about?

149
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,375
[JACK]
And who the hell are you?

150
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,083
[scoffs]

151
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:27,166
Something similar
to what you are.

152
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:28,500
[gasps]

153
00:09:28,583 --> 00:09:29,958
Oh, that's right.

154
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:31,458
You guys are free, aren't you?

155
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:34,541
Well, in that case,

156
00:09:34,625 --> 00:09:36,166
want in on something better?

157
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:38,833
[RUI groaning in pain]

158
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:41,708
[RUI, weakly]
Boss.

159
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,250
[groaning continues]

160
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,125
What the hell?!

161
00:09:45,208 --> 00:09:46,208
[grunts]

162
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:50,416
All right, what'd you do to him?

163
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:53,333
Answer me!

164
00:09:54,625 --> 00:09:56,541
You just never learn.

165
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:57,833
[gasps]

166
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:00,041
[YUKI sobs]

167
00:10:00,125 --> 00:10:03,166
[SOUMA] Go ahead,
hurry up and finish him.

168
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,958
Do it, Tsubasa.

169
00:10:05,041 --> 00:10:07,458
♪

170
00:10:10,125 --> 00:10:11,750
[groaning]

171
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:15,833
[screaming]

172
00:10:24,208 --> 00:10:25,083
[SUMIRE gasps]

173
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:26,791
-[BOTH gasp]
-Sumire, no!

174
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:29,291
[groaning]

175
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:30,541
[screams, gasps]

176
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,291
[groaning]

177
00:10:34,916 --> 00:10:37,458
[grunting in effort]

178
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,416
It's that guy.

179
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,791
[YUKI]
Akira!

180
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:48,291
[muffled groaning]

181
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:51,791
[AKIRA, weakly]
Miss Yuki, be strong.

182
00:10:51,875 --> 00:10:54,416
You have to use your will.

183
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,125
You can do it.

184
00:10:58,041 --> 00:11:00,500
[YUKI crying]

185
00:11:00,583 --> 00:11:01,666
No, I can't.

186
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,375
I can't.

187
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:08,416
[SOUMA]
You're wasting your time, Akira.

188
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:09,916
It's impossible for you.

189
00:11:10,916 --> 00:11:13,500
You cannot protect anyone.

190
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:14,458
[gasps]

191
00:11:16,083 --> 00:11:17,416
[groaning sharply]

192
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,416
No! Stop it!

193
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,541
[groans sharply]

194
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:21,833
[YOSHIAKI]
Stop this, right now!

195
00:11:21,916 --> 00:11:23,791
Forgive me, I've failed.

196
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:34,166
[YOSHIAKI]
I think that's enough.

197
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:38,291
Aw, what's got you down,
my friend?

198
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:41,333
I want you to tell me
what you did to my brother!

199
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:43,875
[snickers]

200
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:48,000
[SOUMA]
What do you say, big brother?

201
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,875
Feel up to killing a sibling?

202
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:55,625
Is it really you?

203
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:00,458
[grunts]

204
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:07,833
He's missing me on purpose.

205
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:09,166
[BOTH gasp]

206
00:12:11,291 --> 00:12:12,833
Brother.

207
00:12:12,916 --> 00:12:15,833
♪

208
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:17,583
[SOUMA] What do you think
you're doing?!

209
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:20,375
Hit him properly, now!

210
00:12:20,458 --> 00:12:22,000
[grunts]

211
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:24,000
♪

212
00:12:31,541 --> 00:12:32,833
[SOUMA]
Give it back!

213
00:12:36,458 --> 00:12:38,916
[crying]
Brother, it hurts.

214
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,791
[TSUBASA]
Well, I guess you can't help it.

215
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:43,750
Did you trip on this rock
or something?

216
00:12:44,916 --> 00:12:46,666
Come on, don't cry.

217
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:49,000
Here. Watch this, okay?

218
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:51,166
♪

219
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:57,791
Oh, wow. It disappeared.

220
00:12:57,875 --> 00:12:59,666
Along with those tears, right?

221
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:02,458
[gasps]

222
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:07,708
[YOSHIAKI] Brother,
do you want me to erase this?

223
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,583
[coughs]

224
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:13,250
Where are you?!

225
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:14,250
It's mine!

226
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:15,416
Give it back to me!

227
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,375
♪

228
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,208
[grunting in effort]

229
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:26,333
Stop this!

230
00:13:26,416 --> 00:13:29,125
[YOSHIAKI grunting]

231
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:33,000
[SOUMA groans weakly]

232
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:39,666
[TAKUYA]
Yuki!

233
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:42,166
[YOSHIAKI panting]

234
00:13:47,541 --> 00:13:50,083
♪

235
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:55,833
Hmm.

236
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:03,833
[YOSHIAKI]
Brother.

237
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,416
I'm surprised he's still here.

238
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,208
Tsubasa's Tama-shi.

239
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:13,000
I think he's held here.

240
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:15,458
Their mutual affection

241
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:16,916
keeps them tethered.

242
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:23,208
[TSUBASA] Light of Hope.
Guess we'll see.

243
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:28,166
Be great to find it here.

244
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,458
Hope, that is.

245
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,791
-[excited chatter]
-[laughter]

246
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,708
I heard we're getting
plastic models today.

247
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:40,166
-Amazing.
-[BOY] All right!

248
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:43,208
♪

249
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:55,083
[DOCTOR 1]
He shows some potential.

250
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:58,083
[DOCTOR 2]
Maybe, but you have to admit,

251
00:14:58,166 --> 00:15:01,041
number 57
has quite a bit more.

252
00:15:01,125 --> 00:15:02,541
[DOCTOR 1]
You mean the little brother?

253
00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:05,250
-[glass shatters]
-Huh?

254
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:08,250
[DOCTOR 2] Hey, number 24.
What do you think you're doing?

255
00:15:10,791 --> 00:15:12,333
[groans]

256
00:15:12,416 --> 00:15:13,541
[DOCTOR 1]
Let go!

257
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:16,208
[ALL gasp]

258
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,333
[DOCTOR 2]
Whoa. It disappeared.

259
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:20,750
[DOCTOR 1]
What does this mean?

260
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,333
[TAIYO]
What happened?

261
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,791
[DOCTOR 3]
The artifact, it disappeared.

262
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:29,583
Oh?

263
00:15:29,666 --> 00:15:31,208
Well, it's not the power
we're looking for,

264
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:34,041
but it seems like
a useful one.

265
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:36,166
Very useful, indeed.

266
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:38,875
♪

267
00:15:44,041 --> 00:15:45,958
[TSUBASA]
I should be enough for them,

268
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:47,750
they don't need you, too.

269
00:15:49,083 --> 00:15:51,875
Yoshiaki. I swear to you,

270
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:54,208
I will erase all the Artifacts
in this world

271
00:15:54,291 --> 00:15:56,291
before your power awakens.

272
00:15:58,166 --> 00:15:59,291
If I do that,

273
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,791
then, you'll be free.

274
00:16:09,041 --> 00:16:10,375
It's okay.

275
00:16:10,458 --> 00:16:12,458
We'll all survive if you wanna
rest like this

276
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:13,833
every once in a while.

277
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:15,250
[TSUBASA breathes heavily]

278
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:18,208
Sorry. I'll pull my weight
next time.

279
00:16:18,291 --> 00:16:21,041
But seriously,
how'd you guys manage it?

280
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:22,875
[laughs]

281
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:23,916
[TSUBASA]
Huh?

282
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,208
What is it?

283
00:16:25,291 --> 00:16:27,041
[TSUBASA laughing]

284
00:16:27,125 --> 00:16:29,875
This it's a fake.

285
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:32,166
-[RUI] What?!
-[KANA gasps]

286
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:35,416
[JACK] That has to mean
that they knew we were after it.

287
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,958
[KANA]
How? No way.

288
00:16:38,041 --> 00:16:39,875
-[TSUBASA] Eh, don't worry.
-[ALL] Hmm?

289
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:42,375
This is still pretty nice.

290
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:44,041
It's a good little trinket.

291
00:16:45,541 --> 00:16:46,416
See?

292
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:49,041
It's beautiful up there.

293
00:16:49,125 --> 00:16:51,625
I knew this chandelier
was missing something.

294
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:58,041
[panting]

295
00:17:01,166 --> 00:17:03,583
[keys clacking]

296
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:05,833
♪

297
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:10,166
[gasps]

298
00:17:16,958 --> 00:17:18,583
Where are you?

299
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:20,625
Taiyo!

300
00:17:20,708 --> 00:17:22,666
Give Yoshiaki back!

301
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,666
Give him back!

302
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:27,666
[gasps]

303
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:30,875
Yoshiaki.

304
00:17:30,958 --> 00:17:33,208
♪

305
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:50,625
My brother, thank you.

306
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:55,375
I... I just never knew.

307
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:11,125
[RUI]
Thanks, boss.

308
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:13,875
I hope we meet again.

309
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:16,833
Huh?

310
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:19,041
Huh?

311
00:18:19,125 --> 00:18:21,250
Holy crap, is that...

312
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:24,541
[BOTH laugh]

313
00:18:24,625 --> 00:18:26,916
[RUI]
He still had it, after all that.

314
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,250
[JACK]
Not funny. Show some respect.

315
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,208
-[SOUMA groaning]
-[JACK] Huh?

316
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:34,583
Hey, look who's awake.
Mornin', kiddo.

317
00:18:34,666 --> 00:18:37,000
I'll be happy to cut him up.

318
00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:38,208
-[YUKI] Wait.
-[ALL] Hmm?

319
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:40,041
[SOUMA groaning]

320
00:18:40,125 --> 00:18:42,041
[YUKI]
Come back to me, Souma.

321
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:45,833
[SOUMA, weakly]
You haven't changed, sis.

322
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:48,833
You always think you know best.

323
00:18:48,916 --> 00:18:50,125
Even now.

324
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:52,375
You know what?

325
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:55,416
I hate that part of you.

326
00:18:57,500 --> 00:19:00,291
[scoffs]
You do this thing.

327
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:03,958
You carry yourself as if only
you can save everyone.

328
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:04,958
[inaudible]

329
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:07,500
♪

330
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:10,958
[grunts softly]

331
00:19:11,041 --> 00:19:13,750
[SOUMA]
What do you know...

332
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,875
about what I can bear?

333
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:18,750
Was I always just
a weight on your back?

334
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:21,250
Don't treat me like
I'm still a child!

335
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:24,666
You're the one
who should come with me.

336
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:26,916
I'll be the one to save you.

337
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,500
I will. I have to...

338
00:19:37,791 --> 00:19:39,583
I'm sorry.

339
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:41,750
Forgive me, Souma.

340
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:44,375
[weeping]
I didn't understand.

341
00:19:44,458 --> 00:19:46,250
I never knew you felt this way.

342
00:19:47,583 --> 00:19:50,000
♪

343
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:56,791
That's why I told you.

344
00:19:56,875 --> 00:20:00,708
Not only did Souma's plan fail,
our enemies have him now.

345
00:20:00,791 --> 00:20:03,333
It's a very upsetting
state of affairs.

346
00:20:03,416 --> 00:20:06,833
So, then, tell me how you
didn't see this coming

347
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:08,625
with your powers?

348
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,125
Why didn't you tell us?

349
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:13,583
Wasn't this the result
you wanted?

350
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:14,791
[TSUKI]
Hmm?

351
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:18,625
♪

352
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:27,625
I have no idea when he will
regain consciousness.

353
00:20:27,708 --> 00:20:29,458
But as long as
he keeps resting here,

354
00:20:29,541 --> 00:20:32,000
his body should recover,
I feel certain of that.

355
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:35,958
[TAKUYA] We have do something
about this soon.

356
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,958
Before the Agency
takes him back.

357
00:20:45,458 --> 00:20:46,833
[TAKUYA]
Sorry I'm late.

358
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:48,958
[YOSHIAKI]
Not at all.

359
00:20:49,041 --> 00:20:50,458
This way.

360
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:52,125
[YOSHIAKI]
Hey.

361
00:20:52,208 --> 00:20:53,958
Are you really planning to go?

362
00:20:54,041 --> 00:20:56,583
I mean, if he were
to wake up right now...

363
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:57,958
[TAKUYA]
Yeah, that's why we're leaving

364
00:20:58,041 --> 00:20:59,916
before he regains consciousness.

365
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,333
I want to do what I can,
and to do that,

366
00:21:03,416 --> 00:21:07,166
I need some solid proof
of his relationship with them.

367
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:08,375
Will you come with me?

368
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,958
[KEIGO]
Hey, you must be Takuya.

369
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:19,208
[TAKUYA] So these were
the guys watching me?

370
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:22,458
Yeah, we know you're very sharp,
but we're not the enemy.

371
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:25,041
We'd like to go with you

372
00:21:25,125 --> 00:21:28,250
to the Light of Hope Academy
for Children with Disabilities.

373
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:29,500
[BOTH gasp]

374
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:32,541
[YUJI]
Our friend was murdered.

375
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:37,208
[KEIGO]
We're not after you guys, okay?

376
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:43,333
So that's how it is.

377
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:46,333
[YUKI]
Yumiko.

378
00:21:47,916 --> 00:21:50,458
[YUMIKO]
Sorry, did I wake you?

379
00:21:50,541 --> 00:21:51,750
Where's Takuya?

380
00:21:53,583 --> 00:21:57,125
[YUMIKO] Well, I don't know,
he went out pretty far today.

381
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:58,333
[YUKI]
Huh?

382
00:22:01,083 --> 00:22:03,416
[YUMIKO]
Looks like it finally got him.

383
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:05,416
It's time to face his past.

384
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,208
♪

385
00:23:43,250 --> 00:23:45,791
[TAKUYA]
Next episode, "Regret."

